description:
`PmUlInterferenceReport`:  Table containing uplink interference reports for a radio access network.

`dateTime`: Timestamp of the interference report.
`Area_Name`: Geographic area where the interference occurred (e.g., cell site location).
`CellId`: Unique identifier for the cell experiencing interference.
`Id2`:  Duplicate of CellId.  Redundant column.
`Id3`:  Ancillary identifier, likely related to interference source or type.
`Id4`: Ancillary identifier, likely related to interference source or type.
`vsDataType`:  Data type identifier, indicating the report's type.
`vsDataFormatVersion`: Version of the data format used for the report.
`PmUlInterferenceReport.rfBranchRxRef`:  Reference to the receiving radio frequency branch experiencing interference, containing hierarchical location information.
`PmUlInterferenceReport.pmUlInterferenceReportId`:  Unique identifier for the specific interference report instance.
